<TEXT>&#2;<DATELINE>2010-03-25</DATELINE><TITLE>The challenges of public health education with a particular reference to China</TITLE><BODY>A recent seminar on public health education at the Chinese University of Hong Kong posed some key questions for the future of public health, as well as how the next generation of public health specialists should be educated. This paper summarizes some of the discussions on the future of public health education in China within the context of China's healthcare reforms and trends in global public health education.&#3;</BODY></TEXT>